        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 8 at 9:11PM CDT until September 8 at 10:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Wheeler County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northeastern Gray County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Roberts County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1015 PM CDT.

* At 911 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles northwest
of Lora, or 9 miles north of Miami, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Tennis ball size hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile
homes, roofs, and outbuildings. People and animals
outdoors will be injured. Expect hail damage to roofs,
siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Miami, Codman, and Lora.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
